    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
        The application uses a tabbed navigation structure to separate content by month and additional sections (Tools, Extra Skills). 
        This mirrors the chronological and thematic organization of the source report, making it intuitive for users to follow their learning path.
        Each task is presented as an interactive checklist item, allowing users to mark their progress. Progress counters are updated dynamically for each section and overall.
        State persistence is handled by Firebase Firestore, saving checkbox states per user.
        This structure was chosen for its clarity, ease of navigation, and the practical utility of progress tracking for a study plan, now enhanced with persistence.
        Key interactions:
        1. Tab clicks to switch between content sections.
        2. Checkbox clicks to mark tasks as complete, triggering UI updates (strikethrough), progress counter recalculations, and saving state to Firestore.
        3. Automatic loading of saved states from Firestore on page load.
    -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
        - Report Title, Period, Goal: Displayed prominently in the header (HTML/Tailwind) for immediate context. Goal: Inform.
        - Monthly & Additional Sections: Organized using tabs (HTML buttons, JS for visibility). Content includes headings and lists of tasks. Goal: Organize, Navigate, Inform.
        - Tasks/Topics: Rendered as interactive list items (`<li>` with checkboxes and unique `data-task-id`). `<code>` tags highlight tools. Goal: Detail, Track. Interaction: Checkboxes. Library: HTML/Tailwind/JS + Firestore for persistence.
        - Progress Tracking: Text-based counters ("X/Y выполнено") for each section and overall. Updated via JS. Goal: Motivate, Summarize. Library: JS.
        - Tools List: A dedicated tab lists all tools/platforms mentioned, extracted from the plan. Goal: Reference. Library: HTML/Tailwind.
        - Justification: This approach presents the information clearly, allows for easy interaction and progress tracking with persistence, and uses simple, effective web technologies.
    -->
